+# CTO Incident - Phase 7.10.z Active Block
+
+GLASSBOX metadata:
+
+- Incident note: `CTO_INCIDENT_20260508T032007Z_PHASE_7_10_Z_BLOCK.md`
+- Remediation phase: `phase-7-10-y-block-remediation-20260508T032007Z`
+- Active block: `outbox/_blocks/phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z.block`
+- Blocked phase: `phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z`
+- Pacer queue timestamp: `2026-05-08T03:20:07Z`
+- Classification: infra-only block, still valid
+
+## Root Cause
+
+The block is a merge-readiness failure, not a scientific-evidence failure.
+
+The blocked worker completed and pushed branch
+`phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z` at
+`f2fbb3f830ed197e904b5a45d62bc64f79d500b3`. Worker-side validation passed and
+the branch diff contains only six new autonomy-backlog `BRIEF.md` files.
+
+Chef then attempted a fast-forward merge into `main` and aborted because the
+branch had diverged from current `origin/main`. The chef log records:
+
+```text
+[2026-05-08T01:58:55+02:00] chef: verify-and-merge phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z (branch phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z)
+fatal: Not possible to fast-forward, aborting.
+```
+
+The panel average was `81`, with concerns focused on failed fast-forward
+mergeability and missing source-of-truth freshness proof. `ADVISOR_CHECK.md` is
+absent; the chef script conservatively defaulted to `BLOCK` after advisor Codex
+returned non-zero.
+
+## Blast Radius
+
+- Chef-daemon remains paused while the active block file exists.
+- Normal scientific queueing remains paused; the pacer is only queuing bounded
+  block-remediation tasks during its cooldown window.
+- Worker daemons, CTO daemon, and chef daemon are alive, but liveness does not
+  clear the merge-readiness block.
+- Watchdog state shows the same active block in `bsebench-async-codex`,
+  `bsebench-async-codex-worker-2`, and `bsebench-async-codex-cto-report`.
+- No thesis files, claim registry files, `claims/registry.yaml`, `claim_55`, or
+  roadmap files were edited by this remediation.
+
